  "story": {
    "logline": "The sole survivor on a dying space station intercepts a signal that changes what it means to be the last of anything.",
    "synopsis": "EVA-7 station, 2147. Radio operator MIRA has been alone for 60 days after the crew evacuation. With power reserves at 4%, she prepares a final log. Then a voice — familiar, impossible — comes through the static. In 90 seconds, she must decide: answer, or let silence win.",
    "theme": "The cost of solitude and the courage of connection.",
    "narrative_arc": [
      {
        "act": "Act 1 — Isolation",
        "title": "The Empty Station",
        "description": "Establish Mira alone in the dimly lit comms room. Ambient hum of dying systems. She records her final log entry.",
        "key_events": ["Mira activates recorder", "Power warning flashes"],
        "emotional_tone": "resigned, melancholy",
        "target_length_sec": 30
      },
      {
        "act": "Act 2 — Signal",
        "title": "The Voice",
        "description": "Static breaks. A voice calls her name — her sister, who died on the evacuation shuttle. Mira freezes.",
        "key_events": ["Static spike on scope", "Voice says her name"],
        "emotional_tone": "shocked, yearning",
        "target_length_sec": 30
      },
      {
        "act": "Act 3 — Choice",
        "title": "Answer",
        "description": "Mira reaches for the transmit button. Cut to black. A single LED blinks on — she answered.",
        "key_events": ["Hand on transmit button", "Fade to black", "LED blink"],
        "emotional_tone": "cathartic, open",
        "target_length_sec": 30
      }
    ],
    "characters_summary": ["MIRA — radio operator, 30s, survivor", "VOICE — Mira's sister, heard only (deceased)"]
  },

  "script": {
    "format": "screenplay",
    "full_text": "INT. EVA-7 COMMS ROOM — CONTINUOUS\n\nEmergency lighting. Banks of dead screens. MIRA (30s, flight suit, hollow eyes) sits before the only live console.\n\nMIRA\n(to recorder)\nDay sixty. Power at four percent. This is Mira Osei, final log.\n\nA burst of STATIC. The waveform spikes.\n\nVOICE (V.O.)\n(through static)\nMira...\n\nMira's hand freezes above the controls.\n\nVOICE (V.O.)\nIt's me. Don't be afraid.\n\nMira stares at the transmit button. A long beat.\n\nHer hand moves.\n\nCUT TO BLACK.\n\nA single LED blinks green.\n\nFADE OUT.",
